ear-old%20breathed%20his%20last.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20protest%2C%20they%20punctured%20a%20tyre%20of%20the%20vehicle%20that%20was%20carrying%20the%20deceased%20leader%E2%80%99s%20mortal%20remains%20to%20his%20village.%20The%20issue%20was%2C%20however%2C%20fixed%20quickly.%20It%20was%20evident%20that%20the%20Jamaat%20leadership%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20challenge%20the%20government%20by%20holding%20his%20funeral%20prayers%20in%20the%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20mellowed%20response%20to%20the%20leader%E2%80%99s%20death%20has%20invited%20criticism%20from%20its%20supporters%20at%20the%20grassroots%20level%2C%20more%20so%20because%20Sayeedi%20was%20the%20most%20illustrious%20leader%20in%20the%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20party%20is%20known%20for%20its%20regimented%20nature.%20And%20Jamaat%2C%20though%20an%20Islamist%20party%2C%20is%20structured%20around%20the%20Leninist%20principle%20of%20democratic%20centralism.%20It%20has%20a%20three-tier%20membership%20process%2C%20and%20until%20now%2C%20dissent%20used%20to%20be%20voiced%20only%20in%20party%20forums.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20muted%20response%20is%20surprising%2C%20because%20Sayeedi%2C%20an%20Islamic%20evangelist-turned-politician%2C%20garnered%20some%20degree%20of%20admiration%20across%20the%20country%2C%20despite%20a%20prolonged%20public%20disagreement%20over%20his%20role%20in%201971.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBangladesh%20Chhatra%20League%2C%20the%20student%20wing%20of%20the%20ruling%20Awami%20League%2C%20which%20initiated%20Sayeedi%E2%80%99s%20trial%2C%20suspended%20some%20of%20its%20leaders%20and%20activists%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.prothomalo.com%2Fbangladesh%2Fpolitics%2Fsgx32rsc85%5C%22%3Efor%20mourning%20Sayeedi%E2%80%99s%20death%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20stands%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20Jamaat%20is%20a%20force%20to%20be%20reckoned%20with%20in%20Bangladesh%20and%20is%20getting%20stronger%20by%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20true%20that%20the%20party%2C%20as%20a%20political%20force%2C%20is%20not%20finished%20yet%2C%20but%20with%20over%2023%2C000%20of%20its%20activists%20facing%20cases%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2023%2F08%2Fbangladeshs-jamaat-e-islami-thrives-amid-persecution%2F%5C%22%3E90%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20people%2C%20including%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20current%20top%20leaders%2C%20in%20prison%2C%20Jamaat%20is%20in%20disarray%20and%20in%20no%20position%20to%20put%20up%20a%20strong%20resistance%20in%20the%20streets.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOnly%20in%20June%20this%20year%2C%20the%20party%20was%20allowed%20to%20hold%20a%20public%20meeting%20in%20Dhaka%2C%20the%20first%20of%20its%20kind%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailystar.net%2Fnews%2Fbangladesh%2Fpolitics%2Fnews%2Fjamaat-holds-rally-after-decade-3342761%5C%22%3Ein%20over%20a%20decade%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20rare%20generosity%20the%20government%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20repeated.%20Two%20days%20later%2C%20a%20local%20newspaper%20reported%2C%20quoting%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailystar.net%2Fnews%2Fbangladesh%2Fnews%2Fjamaat-regroups-stealth-3345506%5C%22%3Eanonymous%3C%2Fa%3E%20intelligence%20source%20as%20saying%2C%20that%20Jamaat%20now%20has%20around%2023%20million%20active%20members%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20appears%20to%20be%20highly%20exaggerated%2C%20as%20the%20party%2C%20of%20late%2C%20has%20not%20been%20allowed%20to%20carry%20out%20any%20outdoor%20political%20activity.%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20high%20court%20declared%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fcnews-us-bangladesh-ruling-jamaat-idCABRE9700KH20130801%5C%22%3EJamaat%2C%20a%20political%20party%2C%20illegal%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20it%20conflicted%20with%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20secular%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fwhy-bangladeshs-democracy-is-on-life-support%5C%22%3EWhy%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20Democracy%20Is%20on%20Life%20Support%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20impact%20on%20the%20electoral%20process%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJamaat%20is%20effectively%20barred%20from%20participating%20in%20any%20electoral%20process%20in%20Bangladesh.%20Almost%20all%20of%20its%20major%20leaders%20were%20either%20hanged%20for%20collaborating%20with%20the%20Pakistan%20Army%20during%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20independence%20war%20or%20died%20in%20prison%2C%20serving%20sentences.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThrown%20underground%2C%20Jamaat%E2%80%99s%20programmes%20are%20not%20covered%20in%20national%20newspapers.%20Its%20finances%20are%20in%20tatters.%20The%20party%20now%20is%20a%20skeleton%20of%20its%20previous%20self.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBangladesh%20has%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.prothomalo.com%2Fbangladesh%2Fw586jfvvsk%5C%22%3E119%20million%20voters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20numbers%20do%20not%20look%20good%20for%20the%20party%2C%20if%20it%20goes%20to%20the%20polls%20without%20forming%20an%20electoral%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJamaat%20used%20to%20be%20in%20a%20political%20and%20electoral%20alliance%20with%20the%20Bangladesh%20Nationalist%20Party%20(BNP)%2C%20which%20is%20effectively%20led%20by%20Tarique%20Rahman%2C%20the%20party%20chairperson%20Khaleda%20Zia%E2%80%99s%20first%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFounded%20by%20military%20dictator%20General%20Ziaur%20Rahman%2C%20the%20BNP%20initially%20followed%20a%20centrist%20agenda%2C%20welcoming%20both%20members%20of%20the%20dying%20Muslim%20league%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famitavghosh.com%2Fthe-red-maulana-and-the-last-emperor-of-china-part-1%2F%5C%22%3ERed%20Maulana%3C%2Fa%3E%20Abdul%20Hamid%20Khan%20Bhashani%E2%80%99s%20leftist%20National%20Awami%20Party.%20However%2C%20this%20balancing%20act%20proved%20to%20be%20tricky%2C%20and%20eventually%2C%20the%20party%20inclined%20towards%20right-wing%20politics%20in%202001