2Fdelhi-master-plan-2041-projected-to-be-100-billion-opportunity-potential-to-increase-per-capita-income-to-rs-4-lakh%2Farticleshow%2F103808156.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Delhi%20Master%20Plan%202041%20is%20expected%20to%20unlock%20real%20estate%20potential%20in%20165%20Delhi%20villages%2C%20potentially%20increasing%20Delhi's%20per%20capita%20income%20to%20Rs%204%20lakh.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fdelhi-master-plan-2041-projected-to-be-100-billion-opportunity-potential-to-increase-per-capita-income-to-rs-4-lakh%2Farticleshow%2F103808156.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ramdev's%20Bhartiya%20Shiksha%20Board%20A%20Pan-India%20Education%20Board%20Now%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20circular%20issued%20by%20All%20India%20Council%20for%20Technical%20Education%20(AICTE)%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsb.org.in%2Findex.php%5C%22%3EBhartiya%20Shiksha%20Board%20(BSB)%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20designated%20as%20a%20pan-India%20School%20Education%20Board.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20council%20stated%20that%20BSB%2C%20formed%20in%202019%20and%20approved%20by%20department%20of%20Higher%20Education%20under%20Ministry%20of%20Education%2C%20will%20now%20be%20considered%20equivalent%20to%20other%20national%20boards%20in%20the%20country.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAssociation%20of%20Indian%20Universities%20(AIU)%2C%20accords%20equivalence%20to%20school%20Boards%20in%20India.%20AIU%20has%20accorded%20equivalence%20for%20grade%2010%20and%20and%20grade%2012%20Board%20examination%20qualifications%20of%20Bhartiya%20Shiksha%20Board%20(BSB)%20that%20shall%20function%20as%20a%20regular%20school%20Board%20within%20India.%20You%20are%2C%20therefore%20requested%20to%20consider%20Bhartiya%20Shiksha%20Board%20as%20a%20Pan%20India%20School%20Education%20Board%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aicte-india.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FCircular%2520%25281%2529_3.PDF%5C%22%3Eofficial%20notification%20from%20AICTE%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20official%20website%20of%20BSB%2C%20the%20board%20was%20introduced%20with%20an%20aim%20to%20re-establish%20Indian%20knowledge%20systems.%20The%20website%20mentions%20it%20as%20a%20movement%20against%20'Macaulay's%20toxic%20legacy'%2C%20noting%20that%20this%20legacy%20willfully%20liquidated%20our%20indigenous%20education%20and%20knowledge%20systems%20which%20comprised%20of%20the%20Bhartiya%20Gyan%20Parampara%20and%20the%20Gurukul%20system.%20%26quot%3BThe%20knowledge%20system%20in%20the%20country%20was%20then%20substituted%20with%20the%20western%20culture%20and%20slave%20mindset%20of%20a%20colonised%20nation.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20is%20being%20headed%20by%20Ramdev%20and%20Acharya%20Balkrishna%2C%20the%20co-founder%20of%20yoga%20guru's%20FMCG%20company%20Patanjali.%20Other%20board%20members%20of%20the%20education%20board%20are%20spiritual%20leader%20Morari%20Bapu%2C%20Swami%20Govind%20Giri%20Ji%20(a%20senior%20functionary%20of%20the%20board)%2C%20Shrinivasa%20Varakhedi%20(Upadhyaksha)%2C%20Dr%20Nagendra%20Prasad%20Singh%20(the%20caretaker%20head)%2C%20Dr%20Punam%20Suri%20and%20Giridhar%20Malaviya%20Sadasya.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695204000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2021-04%2Fkjq353h8_baba-ramdev-took-sanyaas-on-ramnavmi-revealed-in-indian-idol-12_625x300_14_April_21.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Feducation%2Framdevs-bhartiya-shiksha-board-a-pan-india-education-board-now-4406845%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20board%20has%20been%20set%20up%20to%20revive%20the%20ancient%20Indian%20knowledge%20system%20and%20blend%20it%20with%20modern%20scientific%20knowledge%20and%20e-learning.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Feducation%2Framdevs-bhartiya-shiksha-board-a-pan-india-education-board-now-4406845%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Feducation%2Framdevs-bhartiya-shiksha-board-a-pan-india-education-board-now-4406845%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Feducation%2Framdevs-bhartiya-shiksha-board-a-pan-india-education-board-now-4406845%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'The%20Timing%2C%20Small%20Fine'%3A%20How%20Anil%20Ambani's%20Relevance%20Diminished%20in%20the%20Reliance%20Home%20Finance%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F04145423%2FAnil-PTI.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20On%20September%2012%2C%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Board%20of%20India%20(SEBI)%20penalised%20Reliance%20Home%20Finance%20with%20Rs%2015%20lakh%20and%20its%20three%20promoters%20Rs%206.5%20lakh%2C%20due%20to%20violations%20of%20some%20regulations%20and%20its%20failure%20to%20disclose%20the%20adverse%20findings%20of%20a%20forensic%20report%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fmoney-and-banking%2Fsebi-penalises-reliance-home-finance-for-violating-lodr-regulations-and-concealing-forensic-report-findings%2Farticle67300509.ece%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EHindu%20BusinessLine%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20order%20marked%20the%20culmination%20of%20a%20show-cause%20notice%20that%20had%20been%20issued%20on%20August%205%2C%202021%2C%20specifically%20targeting%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20lapses%20in%20disclosures%20between%20April%201%2C%202019%2C%20and%20March%2026%2C%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20period%2C%20Reliance%20Home%20Finance%20had%20failed%20to%20make%20essential%20disclosures%20to%20stock%20exchanges.%20These%20disclosures%20were%20vital%20in%20assessing%20the%20security%20of%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20debt%20instruments.%20The%20consequences%20of%20these%20lapses%20affected%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20stock%20price%2C%20which%20plummeted%20from%20a%20high%20of%20Rs%2031%20in%20April%202019%20to%20a%20mere%20Rs%200.75%20a%20year%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Price%20Waterhouse%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fpwc-anil-ambani-reliance-capital-home-finance%5C%22%3Eresigned%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20auditor%20of%20Reliance%20Capital%20and%20Reliance%20Home%20Finance%20amid%20suspicions%20of%20fraud.%20It%20cited%20an%20inability%20by%20the%20Anil%20Ambani-led%20firms%20to%20satisfactorily%20resolve%20%E2%80%9Ccertain%20observations%2Ftransactions%E2%80%9D%20which%20could%20be%20significant%20or%20material%20to%20the%20financial%20statements%20of%20both%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackstory%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReliance%20Home%20Finance%20had%20borrowed%20a%20staggering%20sum%20of%20over%20Rs%2012%2C000%20crore%20from%20banks%20and%20investors%2C%20only%20to%20later%20default%20on%20its%20obligations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20violating%20SEBI%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftaxguru.in%2Fsebi%2Fdetailed-analysis-regulation-30-sebi-lodr-regulations-2015.html%5C%22%3ELODR%3C%2Fa%3E%20norms%2C%20or%20Listing%20Obligation%20and%20Disclosure%20Requirements%2C%20which%20say%20that%20a%20listed%20entity%20shall%20disclose%20to%20stock%20exchange(s)%20all%20events%20or%20information%2C%20which%20are%20material%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20reasonably%20possible%20and%20not%20later%20than%2024%20hours%20from%20the%20occurrence%20of%20event%20or%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20SEBI%20regulation%20enables%20transparency%20and%20fair%20disclosures%20by%20all%20listed%20entities%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20debt%20resolution%20process%2C%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20lenders%2C%20in%20August%202019%2C%20had%20appointed%20Grant%20Thornton%20to%20conduct%20an%20independent%20forensic%20audit.%20This%20procedure%20is%20a%20mandatory%20requirement%20as%20per%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%20guidelines%20for%20the%20Prudential%20Framework%20for%20Resolution%20of%20Stressed%20Assets%20in%20cases%20involving%20a%20change%20of%20control%20and%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202020%2C%20the%20auditor%20said%20that%20it%20found%20%E2%80%9Canomalies%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20credit%20appraisal%20process%20of%20the%20company.%20It%20noted%20that%20more%20than%2080%25%20of%20the%20loans%20were%20corporate%20loans%2C%20which%20were%20disbursed%20to%20a%20group%20of%2047%20borrowers%20that%20shared%20these%20common%20characteristics%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fbanking%2Ffinance%2Freliance-home-finance-gave-rs-12000-crore-loans-to-indirectly-linked-borrowers-forensic-audit%2Farticleshow%2F73220535.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ehad%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20people%20aware%20of%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20auditor%20also%20found%20that%20eight%20of%20the%2047%20borrowers%20were%20%E2%80%9Crelated%20parties%E2%80%9D%20of%20Reliance%20Group%20companies%2C%20Reliance%20Power%20and%20Reliance%20Infrastructure%20Ltd%2C%20prior%20to%20disbursal%20of%20loans%20worth%20Rs%201%2C300%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20auditor%20also%20found%20instances%20where%20loans%20granted%20to%20the%20group%20of%2047%20borrowers%20eventually%20found%20their%20way%20back%20to%20Anil%20Ambani%20group%20companies%20through%20onward%20lending%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20reported%2C%20citing%20the%20people%20quoted%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthemorningcontext.com%2Fbusiness%2Fanil-ambani-may-just-go-scot-free%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EMorning%20Context%3C%2Fem%3E%20noted%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20analysis%20published%20on%20September%2020%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20forensic%20audit%20not%20only%20outlined%20the%20movement%20of%20funds%20raised%20from%20investors%20to%20several%20promoter-linked%20companies%2C%20but%20also%20to%20the%20family%20of%20Rana%20Kapoor%2C%20then%20the%20CEO%20of%20Yes%20Bank%2C%20a%20lender%20to%20Reliance%20Home%20Finance.%E2%80%9D%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthemorningcontext.com%2Fbusiness%2Fanil-ambani-may-just-go-scot-free%5C%22%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKapoor%20has%20been%20in%20jail%20since%20March%202020%20in%20connection%20with%20various%20cases%20of%20fraud.%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CA%20similar%20transaction%20between%20Kapoor%20and%20Dewan%20Housing%20Finance%20landed%20its%20promoters%2C%20Kapil%20and%20Dhiraj%20Wadhawan%2C%20in%20jail%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fbook-excerpt-the-unravelling-of-anil-ambanis-empire%5C%22%3EBook%20Excerpt%3A%20The%20Unravelling%20of%20Anil%20Ambani%E2%80%99s%20Empire%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20lapses%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20outlet%20noted%20how%20Anil%20Ambani%20may%20just%20go%20scot%20free%20and%20said%20%E2%80%9Cthough%20the%20company%20was%20promoted%20by%20Anil%20Ambani%2C%20SEBI%E2%80%99s%20show-cause%20notice%20was%20directed%20against%20the%20company%20and%20three%20of%20its%20top%20executives%3A%20chief%20executive%20officer%20Sharad%20Sudhalkar%2C%20company%20secretary%20and%20compliance%20officer%20Parul%20Jain%20and%20chief%20financial%20officer%20Pinkesh%20Shah.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20though%20the%20investigation%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20directly%20with%20Anil%20Ambani%20right%20from%20the%20start%2C%20its%20timing%20and%20rather%20meek%20closure%20with%20a%20small%20fine%20will%20go%20a%20long%20way%20in%20helping%20him%20slowly%20wriggle%20out%20of%20the%20mess%20caused%20in%20the%20company%20over%20the%20years.%20Of%20course%2C%20lapses%20in%20disclosures%20or%20other%20regulatory%20filings%20are%20in%20general%20treated%20as%20the%20fault%20of%20the%20key%20managerial%20personnel.%20But%20in%20this%20case%2C%20I%20strongly%20believe%20Ambani%20should%20have%20been%20a%20party%20to%20the%20investigation%20as%20the%20problems%20in%20the%20company%20started%20with%20the%20debenture%20funds%20being%20routed%20to%20companies%20related%20to%20the%20promoters%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Morning%20Context%3C%2Fem%3E%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThough%20SEBI%E2%80%99s%20investigation%20was%20in%20the%20works%20for%20nearly%20two%20years%2C%20its%20final%20order%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Ambani%20is%20no%20longer%20Reliance%20Home%20Finance%E2%80%99s%20promoter%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Freliance-home-finance-insolvency-supreme-court-allows-debenture-holders-to-be-covered-under-resolution-plan-of-authum-investments-223316%5C%22%3Ewas%20acquired%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Authum%20Investment%20and%20Infrastructure%2C%20under%20the%20bankruptcy%20resolution%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20gravity%20of%20the%20case%2C%20SEBI%20had%20not%20conducted%20an%20in-person%20meeting%20with%20the%20company%20officials%2C%20which%20is%20typically%20a%20mandatory%20requirement%20for%20a%20final%20order%2C%20the%20news%20outlet%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20significant%20delays%20in%20the%20proceedings%2C%20as%20the%20company%20had%20filed%20a%20settlement%20application.%20It%20took%20six%20months%20for%20the%20company%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20show-cause%20notice%2C%20and%20even%20then%2C%20SEBI%20faced%20difficulties%20in%20obtaining%20necessary%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmid%20these%20developments%2C%20as%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20Reliance%20Home%20Finance%20was%20acquired%20by%20Authum.%20This%20rendered%20Anil%20Ambani%E2%80%99s%20involvement%20irrelevant%20in%20the%20context%20of%20SEBI%E2%80%99s%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695203152000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F04145423%2FAnil-PTI.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-timing-small-fine-how-anil-ambanis-relevance-diminished-in-the-reliance-home-finance-case%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20noteworthy%20aspect%20of%20this%20case%20is%20that%20it%20unfolded%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Anil%20Ambani%2C%20who%20had%20promoted%20Reliance%20Home%20Finance%2C%20was%20no%20longer%20associated%20with%20the%20company%2C%20a%20news%20report%20pointed%20out%20in%20its%20analysis.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-timing-small-fine-how-anil-ambanis-relevance-diminished-in-the-reliance-home-finance-case%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Siraj%20Reclaims%20No.%201%20Spot%20In%20ICC%20ODI%20Rankings%20After%20Asia%20Cup%20Final%20Heroics%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndian%20speedster%20Mohammed%20Siraj%20on%20Wednesday%20climbed%20eight%20places%20to%20reclaim%20the%20number%20one%20spot%20in%20the%20ODI%20bowler's%20rankings%20ahead%20of%20the%20ICC%20World%20Cup%20which%20begins%20on%20October%205.%20Siraj's%20onslaught%20in%20the%20Asia%20Cup%20final%20bundled%20out%20Sri%20Lanka%20on%2050%20and%20helped%20him%20top%20the%20bowling%20rankings%20chart.%20With%20the%20Asia%20Cup-winning%20spell%20of%206%2F21%2C%20Siraj%20has%20got%20back%20No%201%20position%20which%20he%20lost%20in%20March%20this%20year%20to%20Josh%20Hazlewood.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESiraj%20finished%20the%20tournament%20with%2010%20wickets%20at%20an%20average%20of%2012.2.%20He%20has%20overtaken%20bowlers%20like%20Trent%20Boult%2C%20Rashid%20Khan%20and%20Mitchell%20Starc%20in%20the%20rankings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Afghan%20spin%20duo%20of%20Mujeeb%20Ur%20Rahman%20and%20Rashid%20Khan%20also%20improved%20their%20rankings%20to%20No.%204%20and%20No.%205%20respectively.%20They%20were%20the%20only%20others%20to%20go%20up%20in%20the%20top%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOutside%20that%20space%2C%20South%20Africa's%20Keshav%20Maharaj%20showed%20a%20tremendous%20rise%20after%20returning%20from%20his%20injury.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMaharaj%20helped%20the%20Proteas%20become%20just%20the%20fifth%20side%20to%20win%20a%20five-match%20ODI%20series%20after%20losing%20the%20first%20two%20games%20against%20the%20'Baggy%20Greens'.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20left-arm%20spinner's%204-33%20in%20the%20fifth%20ODI%20gave%20him%20eight%20wickets%20in%20the%20series%20at%20an%20average%20of%2016.87%20and%20an%20economy%20of%20just%204.07%20per%20over.%20He%20is%20currently%20at%2015th%2C%20up%20ten%20places%20from%20his%20previous%20career-high.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChanges%20were%20also%20seen%20in%20the%20ICC%20Men's%20ODI%20Batting%20Rankings.%20Heinrich%20Klaasen%20of%20South%20Africa%20produced%20an%20all-time%20destructive%20ODI%20knock%20against%20Australia%20in%20the%20fourth%20ODI.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20has%20scored%20more%20runs%20in%20an%20ODI%20innings%20at%20a%20higher%20strike-rate%20than%20Klaasen's%20174%20at%20209.64%20in%20Centurion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20helped%20South%20Africa%20to%20a%20164-run%20win%20and%20moved%20Klaasen%2020%20places%20in%20the%20Men's%20ODI%20Batting%20Rankings.%20He%20is%20now%20placed%20ninth.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDawid%20Malan%20was%20dynamic%20in%20England's%20ODI%20series%20against%20New%20Zealand%2C%20being%20the%20highest%20run-scorer%20with%20277%20runs%20at%20an%20average%20of%2092.33%20and%20a%20strike-rate%20of%20105.72.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20batter%2C%20who%20spent%20357%20days%20at%20No.1%20spot%20in%20the%20ICC%20Men's%20T20I%20Batting%20Rankings%20earlier%20in%20his%20career%2C%20is%20placed%20at%20a%20career-best%2013th%20place%20in%20the%20ODI%20Rankings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMalan's%20compatriot%20Ben%20Stokes%2C%20who%20recently%20reversed%20his%20retirement%2C%20celebrated%20his%20ODI%20comeback%20with%20a%20sensational%20knock%20of%20182%20at%20The%20Oval.%20With%20his%20eye-catching%20performances%2C%20Stokes%20has%20reached%20the%2036th%20place%20in%20the%20ODI%20batting%20rankings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695203040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fv7vcgsgg_siraj-afp_625x300_20_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Findias-mohammed-siraj-reclaims-no-1-spot-in-icc-odi-rankings-for-bowlers-after-dream-asia-cup-final-4406751%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20Mohammed%20Siraj%20reclaims%20No.%201%20spot%20in%20ICC%20ODI%20Rankings%20for%20bowlers%20after%20dream%20Asia%20Cup%20final%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A138%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Findias-mohammed-siraj-reclaims-no-1-spot-in-icc-odi-rankings-for-bowlers-after-dream-asia-cup-final-4406751%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Findias-mohammed-siraj-reclaims-no-1-spot-in-icc-odi-rankings-for-bowlers-after-dream-asia-cup-final-4406751%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Findias-mohammed-siraj-reclaims-no-1-spot-in-icc-odi-rankings-for-bowlers-after-dream-asia-cup-final-4406751%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Women's%20Reservation%20Bill%3A%20The%20Issues%20to%20Consider%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2073rd%20and%2074th%20Amendments%20passed%20in%201993%2C%20which%20introduced%20panchayats%20and%20municipalities%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20reserve%20one-third%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20these%20bodies.%20The%20Constitution%20also%20provides%20for%20reservation%20of%20seats%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%20for%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SCs)%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(STs)%20in%20proportion%20to%20their%20number%20in%20the%20population.%20The%20Constitution%20does%20not%20provide%20for%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies.%20Some%20members%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20had%20opposed%20reserving%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20legislatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E15%25%20of%20the%20total%20members%20of%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20are%20women%20while%20in%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20women%20on%20average%20constitute%209%25%20of%20the%20total%20members.%20In%202015%2C%20the%20Report%20on%20the%20Status%20of%20Women%20in%20India%20noted%20that%20the%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20state%20assemblies%20and%20Parliament%20continues%20to%20be%20dismal.%20It%20noted%20that%20decision%20making%20positions%20in%20political%20parties%20have%20negligible%20presence%20of%20women.%20It%20recommended%20reserving%20at%20least%2050%25%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20local%20bodies%2C%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20Parliament%2C%20ministerial%20levels%2C%20and%20all%20decision-making%20bodies%20of%20the%20government.6%20The%20National%20Policy%20for%20the%20Empowerment%20of%20Women%20(2001)%20had%20stated%20that%20reservation%20will%20be%20considered%20in%20higher%20legislative%20bodies.7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBills%20amending%20the%20Constitution%20to%20reserve%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20Parliament%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%20have%20been%20introduced%20in%201996%2C%201998%2C%201999%2C%20and%202008.%20The%20first%20three%20Bills%20lapsed%20with%20dissolution%20of%20their%20respective%20Lok%20Sabhas.%20The%202008%20Bill%20was%20introduced%20in%20and%20passed%20by%20Rajya%20Sabha%20but%20it%20also%20lapsed%20with%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%2014th%20Lok%20Sabha.%20The%201996%20Bill%20had%20been%20examined%20by%20a%20Joint%20Committee%20of%20Parliament%2C%20while%20the%202008%20Bill%20was%20examined%20by%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Personnel%2C%20Public%20Grievances%2C%20Law%20and%20Justice.%20Both%20Committees%20agreed%20with%20the%20proposal%20to%20reserve%20seats%20for%20women.%20Some%20of%20the%20recommendations%20given%20by%20the%20Committees%20include%3A%20(i)%20considering%20reservation%20for%20women%20belonging%20to%20other%20backward%20classes%20at%20an%20appropriate%20time%2C%20(ii)%20providing%20reservation%20for%20a%20period%20of%2015%20years%20and%20reviewing%20it%20thereafter%2C%20and%20(iii)%20working%20out%20the%20modalities%20to%20reserve%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20councils.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitution%20(One%20Hundred%20and%20Twenty-Eighth%20Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%20was%20introduced%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20September%2019%2C%202023.%20The%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20reserve%20one-third%20of%20the%20total%20number%20of%20seats%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%20for%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKey%20features%20of%20the%20Bill%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%96%AA%20Reservation%20for%20women%3A%20The%20Bill%20reserves%2C%20as%20nearly%20as%20may%20be%2C%20one-third%20of%20all%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20and%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20of%20the%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi.%20This%20will%20also%20apply%20to%20the%20seats%20reserved%20for%20SCs%20and%20STs%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20states%20legislatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%96%AA%20Commencement%20of%20reservation%3A%20The%20reservation%20will%20be%20effective%20after%20the%20census%20conducted%20after%20the%20commencement%20of%20this%20Bill%20has%20been%20published.%20Based%20on%20the%20census%2C%20delimitation%20will%20be%20undertaken%20to%20reserve%20seats%20for%20women.%20The%20reservation%20will%20be%20provided%20for%20a%20period%20of%2015%20years.%20However%2C%20it%20shall%20continue%20till%20such%20date%20as%20determined%20by%20a%20law%20made%20by%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%96%AA%20Rotation%20of%20seats%3A%20Seats%20reserved%20for%20women%20will%20be%20rotated%20after%20each%20delimitation%2C%20as%20determined%20by%20a%20law%20made%20by%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIssues%20to%20consider%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20of%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20legislatures%20can%20be%20examined%20from%20three%20perspectives%3A%20(i)%20whether%20the%20policy%20of%20reservation%20for%20women%20can%20act%20as%20an%20effective%20instrument%20for%20their%20empowerment%2C%20(ii)%20whether%20alternate%20methods%20of%20increasing%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20legislatures%20are%20feasible%2C%20and%20(iii)%20whether%20there%20are%20any%20issues%20with%20the%20proposed%20method%20for%20reservation%20in%20the%20Bill.%20The%20analysis%20in%20this%20section%20is%20largely%20based%20on%20our%20earlier%20Brief%20published%20on%20the%202008%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPurpose%20of%20reservation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20group%20is%20not%20represented%20proportionately%20in%20the%20political%20system%2C%20its%20ability%20to%20influence%20policy-making%20is%20limited.%20The%20Convention%20on%20the%20Elimination%20of%20All%20Forms%20of%20Discrimination%20Against%20Women%20provides%20that%20discrimination%20against%20women%20must%20be%20eliminated%20in%20political%20and%20public%20life.%20While%20India%20is%20a%20signatory%20to%20the%20Convention%2C%20discrimination%20in%20matters%20of%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20decision-making%20bodies%20has%20continued.%20The%20number%20of%20women%20MPs%20has%20increased%20from%205%25%20in%20the%20first%20Lok%20Sabha%20to%2015%25%20in%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%3B%20but%20the%20number%20continues%20to%20be%20quite%20low.%20A%202003%20study%20about%20the%20effect%20of%20reservation%20for%20women%20in%20panchayats%20showed%20that%20women%20elected%20under%20the%20reservation%20policy%20invest%20more%20in%20the%20public%20goods%20closely%20linked%20to%20women%E2%80%99s%20concerns.%20The%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Personnel%2C%20Public%20Grievances%2C%20Law%20and%20Justice%20(2009)%20had%20noted%20that%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20local%20bodies%20has%20enabled%20them%20to%20make%20meaningful%20contributions.%20It%20also%20noted%20that%20concerns%20regarding%20women%20being%20proxies%20to%20men%20in%20local%20bodies%20have%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20baseless.%20The%20Inter-Parliamentary%20Union%20(2022)%20has%20noted%20that%20legislated%20quotas%20have%20been%20a%20decisive%20factor%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20representation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOpponents%20of%20the%20reservation%20policy%20argue%20that%20separate%20constituencies%20for%20women%20would%20not%20only%20narrow%20their%20outlook%20but%20lead%20to%20perpetuation%20of%20unequal%20status%20because%20they%20would%20be%20seen%20as%20not%20competing%20on%20merit.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20Renuka%20Ray%20argued%20against%20reserving%20seats%20for%20women%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20there%20is%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20women%2C%20the%20question%20of%20their%20consideration%20for%20general%20seats%2C%20however%20competent%20they%20may%20be%2C%20does%20not%20usually%20arise.%20We%20feel%20that%20women%20will%20get%20more%20chances%20if%20the%20consideration%20is%20of%20ability%20alone.%E2%80%9D%20Opponents%20also%20argue%20that%20reservation%20would%20not%20lead%20to%20political%20empowerment%20of%20women%20because%20larger%20issues%20of%20electoral%20reforms%20such%20as%20measures%20to%20check%20criminalisation%20of%20politics%2C%20internal%20democracy%20in%20political%20parties%2C%20and%20influence%20of%20black%20money%20have%20not%20been%20addressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlternate%20methods%20of%20representation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReservation%20of%20one-third%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20Parliament%20would%20restrict%20the%20choice%20of%20voters%20in%20the%20reserved%20constituencies.%20Two%20alternatives%20have%20been%20suggested%20by%20some%20experts%3A%20reservation%20for%20candidates%20within%20political%20parties%20(as%20some%20countries%20do%2C%20see%20Table%201)%3B%20and%20dual%20member%20constituencies%20where%20some%20constituencies%20shall%20have%20two%20candidates%2C%20one%20being%20a%20woman%20(see%20Table%202).%20Initially%2C%20India%20had%20multi-member%20constituencies%20which%20included%20an%20SC%2FST%20member.%20A%201961%20Act%20converted%20all%20constituencies%20into%20single%20member%20constituencies.%20The%20reasoning%20was%20that%20the%20constituencies%20were%20too%20large%20and%20SC%2FST%20members%20felt%20that%20they%20would%20gain%20in%20importance%20in%20single-%20member%20reserved%20constituencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131512%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.14.53-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22634%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131512%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.14.53-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131512%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.14.53-PM-300x195.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131512%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.14.53-PM-1024x664.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673890%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22411%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131622%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.16.11-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22725%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131622%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.16.11-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131622%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.16.11-PM-300x126.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131622%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.16.11-PM-1024x430.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673891%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22304%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%203%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERotating%20constituencies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%203%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20states%20that%20reserved%20seats%20shall%20be%20allotted%20by%20rotation%20after%20every%20delimitation%20exercise.%20This%20implies%20rotation%20approximately%20every%2010%20years%20as%20after%202026%20delimitation%20is%20mandated%20to%20take%20place%20after%20every%20census.%20Rotation%20of%20reserved%20seats%20may%20reduce%20the%20incentive%20for%20MPs%20to%20work%20for%20their%20constituencies%20as%20they%20could%20be%20ineligible%20to%20seek%20re-election%20from%20that%20constituency.%20A%20study%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Panchayati%20Raj%20recommended%20that%20rotation%20of%20constituencies%20should%20be%20discontinued%20at%20the%20panchayat%20level%20because%20almost%2085%25%20women%20were%20first-timers%20and%20only%2015%25%20women%20could%20get%20re-elected%20because%20the%20seats%20they%20were%20elected%20from%20were%20de-reserved.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKey%20changes%20between%202008%20and%202023%20Bills%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E