e%20ICRIER%20report%2C%20titled%20%3Cem%3ETackling%20Food%20Inflation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20total%20of%20112%20metric%20tonnes%20of%20wheat%20was%20produced%20in%20the%20country%20in%202022-23.%20In%20the%202023-24%20rabi%20season%2C%20a%20quintal%20of%20wheat%20was%20sold%20at%20a%20minimum%20support%20price%20(MSP)%20of%20Rs%202%2C125%2C%20and%20at%20Rs%202%2C673%20in%20the%20open%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20loss%20incurred%20by%20wheat%20farmers%2C%20the%20report%20says%20that%20the%20government%20had%20launched%20the%20open%20market%20sale%20scheme%20(OMSS)%20in%20February%20this%20year%20to%20sell%20wheat%20at%20a%20substantially%20reduced%20of%20Rs%202%2C350%20per%20quintal%20and%20then%20further%20lower%20at%20Rs%202%2C%20150%20per%20quintal%2C%20with%20an%20intention%20to%20stabilise%20domestic%20prices.%20However%2C%20the%20OMSS%20prices%20were%20significantly%20lower%20than%20the%20cost%20incurred%20by%20farmers%20in%20producing%20wheat%2C%20which%20was%20at%20Rs%202%2C654%20per%20quintal%20in%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWithout%20this%20market%20intervention%2C%20farmers%20could%20have%20potentially%20earned%20an%20additional%20Rs%20548%20per%20quintal%20(Rs%202%2C673%20minus%20Rs%202%2C125)%20from%20their%20sales%20of%20wheat%20resulting%20in%20a%20loss%20of%20around%20Rs%2040%2C000%20crore%20to%20farmers%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20body%20suggested%20the%20government%20use%20trade%20policy%20judiciously%20to%20control%20inflation%20at%20home%20without%20hurting%20farmers%E2%80%99%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695192626000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2F18114942%2FScreen-Shot-2020-04-18-at-11.49.28-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Ffarmers-lost-rs-40000-crore-after-govt-dumped-wheat-in-market-to-check-inflation-report%22%2C%22summary