d%20union%20territories%20in%20June%2C%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Registrar%20General%20of%20India%20(RGI)%2C%20responsible%20for%20conducting%20the%20Census%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fcensus-delayed-deadline-administrative-boundaries-pushed-8697397%2F%5C%22%3Eextended%20the%20deadline%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20freezing%20administrative%20boundaries%20to%20January%201%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20general%20elections%20only%20a%20few%20months%20away%2C%20the%20exercise%20is%20not%20possible%20in%202023%20as%20the%20entire%20government%20machinery%20will%20be%20busy%20preparing%20and%20holding%20elections%20across%20states%20and%20UTs.%20A%20census%20enumeration%20can%20only%20start%20a%20few%20months%20after%20administrative%20boundaries%20are%20established.%20Also%2C%20a%20house-listing%20enumeration%20will%20take%20place%20prior%20to%20the%20census%20to%20conduct%20the%20National%20Population%20Register%20(NPR)%20exercise%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20government%20official%20working%20with%20the%20RGI%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fwomen-reservation-bill-once-again-puts-spotlight-on-much-delayed-census-2021%2Farticleshow%2F103791621.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20NPR%2C%20which%20the%20government%20likely%20has%20plans%20to%20integrate%20with%20the%20upcoming%20Census%2C%20has%20been%20a%20contentious%20issue.%20Critics%20believe%20that%20alongside%20the%20Citizenship%20(Amendment)%20Act%20(for%20which%20the%20Union%20government%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fhome-ministry-seeks-eighth-extension-to-frame-caa-rules%2Farticle67169456.ece%5C%22%3Eyet%20to%20frame%20rules%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20despite%20passing%20the%20Act%20four%20years%20ago)%2C%20the%20NPR%20may%20be%20used%20to%20deny%20Indian%20Muslims%20of%20citizenship.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20the%20government%20claimed%20that%20the%20Census%20was%20delayed%20because%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20However%2C%20in%20the%20years%20since%2C%20all%20activities%20have%20resumed%20to%20full%20capacity%20and%20multiple%20state%20elections%20have%20been%20held.%20The%20Registrar%20General%20of%20India%20has%20not%20announced%20why%20it%20has%20not%20conducted%20the%20Census%20despite%20the%20pandemic%20no%20longer%20coming%20in%20the%20way%20of%20any%20administrative%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20time%20since%20the%20last%20Census%20was%20conducted%2C%20India%20has%20overtaken%20China%20to%20become%20the%20most%20populous%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Findia-china-highest-populated%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20UN%20projections%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20since%20the%20country%20has%20not%20enumerated%20its%20own%20population%2C%20government%20data%20cannot%20confirm%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20February%20this%20year%2C%20when%20finance%20minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20announced%20the%20Budget%2C%20observers%20noticed%20that%20the%20allocation%20for%20census-related%20activities%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fbudget-2023-rs-1-564-crore-allocated-for-census-2021-101675243599156.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIt%2520is%2520part%2520of%2520the%2Cin%2520the%2520Parliament%2520on%2520Wednesday.%5C%22%3Ehad%20been%20cut%20drastically%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20allocation%20the%20year%20before.%20Budget%202022-23%20had%20put%20aside%20Rs%203%2C676%20crore%20for%20such%20activities%2C%20while%20Budget%202023-24%20put%20aside%20Rs%201%2C564%20crore.%20However%2C%20the%20revised%20estimate%20for%202022-23%20was%20even%20lower%20than%20the%20allocation%20for%202023-24%3A%20Rs%20552.65%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20delayed%20Census%20exercise%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20implications%20this%20has%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20citizens%20%E2%80%93%20has%20come%20under%20scrutiny%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years.%20Renowned%20economic%20Pronab%20Sen%2C%20who%20has%20been%20named%20as%20head%20of%20the%20government%20panel%20set%20up%20to%20review%20statistical%20surveys%20and%20suggest%20improvements%2C%20says%20all%20data%20generated%20by%20the%20government%20%E2%80%93%20on%20jobs%2C%20unemployment%2C%20inflation%2C%20etc.%20%E2%80%93%20is%20effected%20by%20the%20lack%20of%20Census%20numbers.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20quality%20of%20any%20statistical%20survey%20depends%20on%20census%20data%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fdelay-in-indias-census-hurting-quality-of-survey-reports-says-official%2Farticleshow%2F101942861.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Etold%20Reuters%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20delay%20has%20also%20led%20to%20speculation%20about%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20motivations.%20For%20instance%2C%20an%20article%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffrontline.thehindu.com%2Fthe-nation%2Fwhy-is-the-government-delaying-census-2021%2Farticle66413377.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EFrontline%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January%20noted%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20delay%20could%20be%20tactical.%20It%20is%20possible%20that%20the%20government%20wants%20to%20wriggle%20out%20of%20enumerating%20the%20population%20sizes%20of%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBCs)%20and%20wants%20to%20hold%20back%20until%20the%20general%20elections%20are%20over.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESecond%2C%20the%20findings%20might%20not%20confirm%20the%20hysteria%20about%20growth%20rates%20of%20certain%20religious%20groups%2C%20which%20has%20become%20a%20standard%20campaigning%20trope%20for%20leaders%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20in%20every%20election.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThird%2C%20the%20data%20on%20fertility%20rates%20of%20religious%20groups%20might%20also%20present%20certain%20inconvenient%20truths.%20Four%2C%20the%20claims%20of%20achievements%20in%20human%20development%20and%20access%20to%20amenities%20might%20also%20be%20belied%20by%20census%20data.%20Whatever%20the%20reason%2C%20the%20government%20has%20offered%20no%20credible%20explanation%20for%20delaying%20Census%202021.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695190703000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20114719%2Findia-1723464_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findias-delayed-census-in-the-spotlight-again-as-womens-reservation-will-have-to-wait%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20women's%20reservation%20Bill%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20implemented%20after%20the%20next%20delimitation%20exercise%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20exercise%20is%20predicated%20on%20updated%20Census%20numbers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findias-delayed-census-in-the-spotlight-again-as-womens-reservation-will-have-to-wait%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20India%20Can%20Learn%20From%20TN%20%26amp%3B%20MP%E2%80%99s%20Policies%20to%20Build%20Inclusive%20Schools%20Across%20the%20Country%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20published%20in%20collaboration%20with%20EkStep%20Foundation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%2025%20years%20of%20working%20in%20the%20field%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F325086%2Fhow-does-inclusive-education-in-early-childhood-development-help-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einclusive%20education%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20made%20Sonali%20Saini%20privy%20to%20a%20glaring%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20India%20lacks%20inclusive%20policies%20and%20frameworks.%20The%20issue%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20massive%20struggle%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20implementation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20talk%20on%20inclusion%2C%20but%20%3Cem%3Ehow%20do%20we%20make%20inclusive%20schools%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWithout%20inclusivity%20and%20subsequently%20good%20learning%20opportunities%2C%20India%20faces%20a%20grave%20problem%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20early%20childhood%20care%20and%20development.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20National%20Education%20Policy%20(NEP)%202020%20highlights%20that%20over%20five%20crore%20children%20currently%20in%20elementary%20school%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F309309%2Fcentral-square-foundation-teachers-guide-improves-learning-outcomes-nipun-bharat-mission%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20attained%20foundational%20literacy%20and%20numeracy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20current%20educational%20system%20is%20such%2C%20it%20adds%2C%20that%20once%20a%20student%20falls%20behind%20on%20this%20foundational%20learning%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20maintain%20a%20flat%20learning%20curve%20for%20years%2C%20perpetually%20unable%20to%20catch%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20last%20two%20decades%2C%20Sonali%20and%20her%20organisation%20Sol%E2%80%99s%20ARC%20have%20worked%20to%20understand%20this%20problem%20in%20depth.%20In%202003%2C%20she%20founded%20the%20non-profit%20to%20build%20inclusive%20education%20and%20livelihood%20solutions%20that%20use%20innovative%20tools%20to%20encourage%20better%20learning%20and%20life%20outcomes.%20They%20aim%20to%20make%20these%20solutions%20scalable%2C%20so%20they%20may%20be%20deployed%20through%20partnerships%20with%20stakeholders%20like%20other%20NGOs%2C%20the%20government%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20journey%20has%20been%20about%20%5Bfiguring%20out%5D%20what%20an%20inclusive%20school%20looks%20like%20in%20a%20country%20like%20India%2C%20which%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20very%20high%20resources%2C%20where%20even%20%5Bprocuring%5D%20crayons%2C%20chairs%2C%20tables%20is%20a%20big%20challenge%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sonali%20explains%20in%20conversation%20with%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20they%20have%20impacted%20four%20million%20children%20and%20young%20adults%20with%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20840px)%20100vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sonali%20founded%20the%20non-profit%20SOL's%20Arc%20to%20build%20inclusive%20education%20and%20livelihood%20solutions.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484.jpg%201156w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-330351%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESonali%20founded%20the%20non-profit%20Sol%E2%80%99s%20ARC%20to%20build%20inclusive%20education%20and%20livelihood%20solutions.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20%E2%80%98lifespan%20approach%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20has%20been%20notable%20about%20Sol%E2%80%99s%20ARC%E2%80%99s%20work%20is%20its%20collaboration%20with%20state%20governments%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20to%20improve%20foundational%20literacy%20and%20inclusive%20education.%20These%20interventions%20serve%20as%20examples%20of%20how%20the%20reach%20and%20implementation%20of%20existing%20policies%20can%20be%20widened%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F311679%2Fthings-to-know-jaadui-pitara-play-based-learning-children-national-curriculum-framework%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpact%20lakhs%20of%20children%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20there%20is%20Project%20Ankur%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20building%20Foundational%20Literacy%20(English)%C2%A0%20and%20Numeracy%20(Math)%20through%20an%20inclusive%20curriculum%20for%20teachers%20and%20students%20from%20Class%201%20to%20Class%203.%20This%20has%20been%20done%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20Rajya%20Shiksha%20Kendra%2C%20the%20key%20department%20working%20towards%20the%20state%20FLN%20programme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESol%E2%80%99s%20ARC%20analyses%20that%20non-inclusive%20pedagogy%2C%20non-conceptual%20FLN%20frameworks%2C%20and%20low%20teacher%20capacities%20are%20some%20of%20the%20key%20reasons%20why%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20vulnerable%20children%20are%20not%20learning%20as%20they%20should.%20Sonali%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20look%20at%20%5Bhigh-income%5D%20countries%2C%20their%20solutions%20were%20very%20high%20cost%20%E2%80%94%20assistive%20technology%2C%20accessible%20content%E2%80%A6that%20may%20not%20be%20possible%20in%20a%20country%20like%20ours%2C%20which%20has%20low%20digital%20penetration.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20teacher%20ratio%20and%20the%20special%20educator%20ratios%20are%20abysmal%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%20Government%20data%20suggests%20that%20the%20teacher%20ratio%20has%20fallen%20from%2043%20in%202010-11%20to%2026.3%20in%202020-%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESol%E2%80%99s%20ARC%2C%20she%20says%2C%20focuses%20more%20on%20education%20outcomes%2C%20with%20the%20aim%20to%20subsequently%20increase%20livelihood%20opportunities.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20work%20on%20a%20lifespan%20approach%20because%20only%20working%20on%20education%20may%20not%20be%20sufficient.%20Even%20when%20we%20complete%20education%2C%20if%20the%20children%20are%20still%20sitting%20at%20home%2C%20then%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20point.%20So%20to%20improve%20life%20outcomes%2C%20we%20include%20that%20under%20our%20focus%20for%20age%20groups%20from%205-39.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201280px)%20100vw%2C%201280px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FBeneficiary-survey-Gujarat_11zon-1695189667.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20organisation's%20UDL%20approach%20emphasises%20flexible%20learning%20environments%20that%20accommodate%20individual%20learning%20differences.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FBeneficiary-survey-Gujarat_11zon-1695189667.jpg%201280w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FBeneficiary-survey-Gujarat_11zon-1695189667-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FBeneficiary-survey-Gujarat_11zon-1695189667-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FBeneficiary-survey-Gujarat_11zon-1695189667-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FBeneficiary-survey-Gujarat_11zon-1695189667-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-330354%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20organisation%E2%80%99s%20UDL%20approach%20emphasises%20flexible%20learning%20environments%20that%20accommodate%20individual%20learning%20differences.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMultiple%20children%2C%20multiple%20ways%20to%20learn%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20Project%20Ankur%2C%20the%20organisation%20has%20taken%20on%20a%20Universal%20Design%20for%20Learning%20(UDL)%20approach%20to%20teaching%20and%20learning%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Cgives%20all%20students%20equal%20opportunities%20to%20succeed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUDL%20is%20a%20framework%20that%20emphasises%20flexible%20learning%20environments%20that%20accommodate%20individual%20learning%20differences.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20basically%20says%20%E2%80%98Teach%20in%20multiple%20ways%2C%20allow%20the%20child%20to%20respond%20in%20multiple%20ways%E2%80%99%E2%80%A6the%20teaching-learning%20material%20should%20have%20multiple%20modalities%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Sonali.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20aims%20to%20bring%20flexibility%20in%20these%20arenas%20so%20they%20can%20be%20adjusted%20as%20per%20an%20individual%20learner%E2%80%99s%20strengths%20and%20needs.%20They%20say%20this%20is%20a%20low-tech%2C%20low-cost%20approach%20that%20is%20suitable%20for%20low-resource%20classrooms%20in%20India.%20The%20resources%20to%20teach%20include%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20adaptable%20methods.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20to%20teach%20subtraction%2C%20a%20teacher%20may%20use%20blocks%2C%20number%20lines%2C%20adapted%20worksheets%2C%20and%20flash%20cards.%20%E2%80%9CNow%20you%E2%80%99ve%20exposed%20the%20child%20to%20all%20learning%20methods%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20up%20to%20the%20child%20which%20way%20they%20want%20to%20carry%20forward%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sonali%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20will%20also%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F234203%2Fnew-national-education-policy-2020-pdf-report-cards-marks-grades-score-cce-continuous-evaluation-descriptive-indicators-sai87%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultiple%20ways%20of%20assessment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20way%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20allowing%20different%20children%20with%20different%20abilities%20to%20answer%20the%20same%20question%20in%20their%20own%20way.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20if%20a%20child%20is%20non-verbal%2C%20the%20schools%20are%20not%20relying%20on%20oral%20examinations%20alone.%20Instead%2C%20the%20child%20can%20respond%20by%20pointing%20at%20the%20right%20answer%20or%20writing%20it%20down.%20If%20the%20child%20has%20challenges%20in%20reading%2C%20then%20the%20child%20may%20receive%20assistance%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20reader.%20%E2%80%9CInstructions%20are%20broken%20down%2C%20turned%20into%20visuals%E2%80%A6then%20all%20children%20benefit%20with%20these%20interventions%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20programme%20also%20addressed%20the%20challenge%20of%20multi-grade%20classrooms%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F304738%2Fnational-curriculum-framework-for-foundational-stage-education-children-india-ekstep%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebreaking%20the%20curriculum%20down%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20types%20of%20learning%20environments%20can%20be%20challenging%20owing%20to%20monograde%20teaching%20material%2C%20low%20availability%20of%20teachers%2C%20rigid%20timetables%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20organisation%20estimates%20that%20approximately%2078%25%20of%20primary%20schools%20in%20India%20have%20three%20or%20fewer%20teachers%20for%20all%20grade%20levels.%20%E2%80%9CSo%20we%20made%20multi-grade%20plans%2C%20wherein%20we%20say%20here%20are%20your%20common%20activities%2C%20here%E2%80%99s%20what%20you%20will%20do%20separately%2C%20and%20that%20way%20we%20address%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20teachers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3B%20All%20pictures%20courtesy%3A%20EkStep%20Foundation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695190027000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FFunder-visit-Tamil-nadu--1695189484.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D330342%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sonali%20Saini%20and%20her%20organisation%20Sol%E2%80%99s